message.content: cs.IT, cs.IT is the most likely category as the paper deals with information theory and capacity of channels. Other possible categories could be cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) as the paper mentions the limit as n approaches infinity, cs.DM (discrete mathematics) as the paper deals with discrete memoryless channels, cs.LG (machine learning) as the paper mentions an application in Bayesian optimal experiment design, and cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) as the paper deals with channel transition matrices consisting of independent and identically distributed random variables.
